&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking our &lt;strong&gt;first-ever Partnership Director&lt;/strong&gt; to build and scale CarbonChain’s partner ecosystem. This is a high-impact, entrepreneurial role at the forefront of our go-to-market motion, reporting directly to the Head of Sales and working closely with co-founders, Marketing, and Product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission: &lt;strong&gt;establish, grow, and manage strategic partnerships that generate 7+ figures of pipeline annually&lt;/strong&gt;, with a particular focus on&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Big 4 consultancies and global SIs like Accenture &lt;/strong&gt;as a primary goal, and&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select boutique consultancies and sustainability-focused service providers as a secondary goal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll bring a track record of creating, structuring, and growing partnerships from scratch — including the messy, hands-on work of opening doors, aligning value propositions, and securing executive buy-in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for a builder: someone equally comfortable in the boardroom with global executives and in the trenches working hand-in-hand with boutique SI founders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership Strategy &amp;amp; Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and execute CarbonChain’s partnership strategy, starting with a focus on consultancies and global SIs, scaling to a broader partner ecosystem over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Origination &amp;amp; Deal-Making:&lt;/strong&gt; Initiate and negotiate partnership agreements that unlock pipeline and revenue - you’ll be directly responsible for generating partner-sourced pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; Build strong relationships with senior leaders at partner organizations, ensuring CarbonChain is positioned as a priority partner.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Work cross-functionally to ensure our partners are equipped to market, sell, and deliver CarbonChain’s solutions effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline &amp;amp; Revenue Ownership:&lt;/strong&gt; Set and achieve partnership-driven pipeline targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Intelligence:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the voice of the partner ecosystem internally, sharing insights on market trends, customer needs, and competitive positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt

&lt;h2&gt;About CarbonChain&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Want to work on the most pressing challenge of our generation? If you have experience building exceptional products, know how to execute at scale, and want to help build a company for the long term, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CarbonChain helps the world’s biggest supply chains measure and reduce their carbon emissions, using verified primary data where possible, and robust defaults where it isn’t. We build software that turns messy, real-world operational and supplier information into decision-grade carbon and compliance insights, so teams can act: improve sourcing, meet regulations like CBAM, and deliver credible reporting to customers, investors, and regulators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a product-led company operating in a high-stakes domain. Data quality, auditability, reliability, and trust matter as much as speed. If you enjoy building systems that customers rely on, and shipping improvements that measurably change behaviour across a network, you’ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Our Product&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our platform combines real-world emissions data with our customers&#39; supply chain information to create actionable insights. We help sustainability teams answer critical questions: Where are the emissions hotspots in our supply chain? Which suppliers should we prioritize? What&#39;s the carbon impact of switching vendors or routes?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A major focus of what we’re building right now is supplier engagement and CBAM data management:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;enabling installations (goods producers) to prepare, manage, and share CBAM datasets through guided product carbon accounting workflows;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;improving our supplier database and connection management to support sharing across supply chains;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;and building ingestion pipelines that turn messy customer files into structured, provenance-tracked, insights-ready data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beyond CBAM, our platform supports product and corporate carbon footprinting used by some of the world’s largest commodities producers and traders, helping teams move from data collection to credible reporting and decision-making&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Product Engineer who thrives at the intersection of engineering, product, and customers. This is a full-stack role with a frontend and product focus - you&#39;ll build features that users love and stick around to see how they&#39;re adopted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work closely with Product Managers, commercial team, and customers to ship solutions that solve real problems. We&#39;re looking for someone who&#39;s worked in a startup environment and knows how to move fast, iterate based on feedback, and build with the customer in mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build end-to-end features across the full stack, with a focus on creating polished, intuitive user experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own features from ideation through to user adoption - you&#39;ll help define what we build, ship it, and measure its impact well after go-live and show true customer obsession&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with customers to understand their needs, gather feedback, and validate solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Product Managers and designers to turn ideas into shipped features, making trade-offs and iterating rapidly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with teams outside of Product &amp;amp; Engineering - like Sales, Customer Success, and Carbon Team - to understand how our product is used and what problems need solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build with modern frontend technologies while being comfortable diving into backend work when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to product thinking and help shape our roadmap based on what you&#39;re seeing and hearing from users&lt;/li&gt;

